deck: Marie Delphine Lalaurie (née Macarty or Maccarthy, c. 1775 – c. 1842), more commonly known as Madame LaLaurie, was a Louisiana-born socialite and serial killer known for the torture and murder of slaves.
description:
Born in New Orleans, Lalaurie married three times over the course of her life. She maintained a prominent position in the social circles of New Orleans until April 10, 1834, when rescuers responding to a fire at her Royal Street mansion discovered bound slaves in her attic who showed evidence of torture over a long period. Lalaurie's house was subsequently sacked by an outraged mob of New Orleans citizens, and it is thought that she fled to Paris, where she is believed to have died.

As of 2014, the Royal Street mansion where Lalaurie lived is still standing and is a prominent New Orleans landmark.

deck: Marcus is a resident at The Kingdom.
description:
All Out War

In the defense of the Hilltop, Marcus is stabbed by an unnamed Savior. He is last seen being brought to the Hilltop mansion by Michonne to get checked up on by Harlan.

Later, as more and more injured begin to have the symptoms as if they were bitten, the survivors discover that The Saviors have mucked up their weapons using zombie guts. Harlan quickly comes to the realization that anyone who is injured, no matter how minor, will die. Many of the injured are put down or pass soon after the discovery, it is unknown what happened to Marcus, but it is presumed he succumbed to his injury or was put down.
name: Marcus

deck: Doug is a resident of the Hilltop Colony.
description:
Whispers Into Screams

After Marco returns to the Hilltop without Ken, Doug is assigned along with Dante and another guard to go looking for him.

As the trio search the uncharted territory for Ken, they come across a barn fitting the description Marco had told them where he had left Ken. Despite the uncertainty of Doug, all three set off inside where they discover Marco's beanie, but not Ken. They are soon ambushed by the undead as they begin to make their way into the barn.

Though vastly outnumbered, the trio manage to fight out of the barn and begin to attack the undead back to back. As they begin to thin the numbers of the undead, Doug is distraught as a roamer seemingly strikes out at him with a knife. He cries out that the undead are using weapons. Another soon striking one of the guards in the party.

Doug attempts to retreat but is stabbed in the back before being pounced on and repeatedly stabbed. The other guard is dispatched soon after, leaving Dante to face the new threat alone.
name: Doug

deck: The young son of a murdered Mexican wrestler who uses his spider-powers to fight injustice in a very reckless way.
description: He was the spider-powered son of Arácnido, a famous luchador (Mexican wrestler). When a corrupt wrestler named Escorpión refused to help him in a fixed match, Arácnido was severley injured and died later. Arácnido Jr. learns Escorpión was paid-off to let his father get hurt and vowed to never let anyone else suffer at the hands of evil men. Donning a costume inspired by his father's wrestling mask, Jr. uses his powers to guard the innocent and helpless in Mexico City.

deck: Mike is a member of The Saviors.
description:
Something To Fear

As the survivors from the van are captured, Mike is seen pointing a gun at Rick. An unnamed Savior then orders him to send a signal to Negan. He fires a gunshot into the air, and a few moments later, Negan and the other Saviors arrive. He later witnesses as Negan bashes Glenn's head in.

All Out War

He is seen with Negan when they capture Eugene. Later on, Mike is seen preparing for the assault against the Hilltop Colony with the other Saviors. He then takes part in the assault and once the gate comes down, he rides a motorcycle into the battlefield. Not long after, Rick shoots and kills Mike, his corpse is seen falling off his motorcycle.
name: Mike

deck: David is a member of The Saviors.
description:
Something To Fear

David is seen hiding from Eugene and Abraham as they go to collect supplies to make ammunition. He is seen with a few of Negan's men, motioning them to stay quiet as they spy on Abraham and Eugene passing by. He is later seen at the Alexandria Safe-Zone with Dwight and a few other Saviors trying, unsuccessfully, to gain access. He then retreats with other Saviors and Dwight.

He later assists Negan and several other Saviors on the road by ambushing Rick's group, he is seen pointing a gun at Rick's head. He then watches as Negan beats Glenn's skull in.

All Out War

David is later seen fighting off zombies, alongside Negan and the rest of the Saviors. After the Saviors are forced to retreat back into The Sanctuary, David comes into the room Holly is in, checking in on her. She asks him if she could have some water, and he replies that he'll give her some water, if she has sex with him. David then begins to rip Holly's shirt open and remove her pants, but, Negan walks in. Negan is mad at David for attempting to rape Holly and questions him before stabbing David in the neck, killing him.
name: David

deck: The version of France's 'Guardian of the Republic' pressed into service during the 'Nazi Occupation Era' after the original Guardian, Marc Saint Clair, defected to the Resistance.
description:
Normally there is never more than ONE 'Garde Republicain' at any one time in the title's long history of service, but when the Vichy Regime sided with the Nazis in 1940, the true Guardian (Marc Saint Clair) promptly defected to the French Resistance. This led to Vichy Minister Pierre Laval deciding to bring in their own version of the champion. They chose Bernard de Sault, an agent of it's Milice (far-right Paramilitary Organization that existed at that time) to don the mantle.

What he lacked in the rigorous training, Bernard made up for it with vicious sadism and steroids to compete with the true article (who was going by the codename "Maquis") as they battled for the fate of France during World War 2.

His tenure was ended, along with his life, in 1944 during the closing days of the War.
name: Guardian of the Republic of Vichy
